38c0/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca352-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::f10a2c40-299f-11f0-8a1c-09e52f3238c0/{imageVariant}"],"make":"Sunseeker","model":"Sunseeker 82 Predator","maxCrew":3,"sleeps":8,"basePort":{"uri":"a::place::084d40a6-b3ee-11ed-af25-325096b39f47","name":"Poltu Quatu","coordinates":{"latitude":41.13557795,"longitude":9.496307881},"country":"Italy"},"cruisingCapacity":12,"builtYear":2007,"architect":"","interiorDesigner":"Sunseeker","refitYear":2024,"topSpeed":35,"cruiseSpeed":24,"fuelCapacity":0,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Double Cabins","value":"2"},{"label":"Twin Cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"Bunk Bed Cabin","value":"1"}],"cabins":4,"bathrooms":4,"length":25,"beam":5.9,"draft":1.72,"hullType":"","hullConstruction":"","tonnage":0,"superStructure":[],"engines":"MTU 2 x 1822 HP","amenities":[{"label":"Air conditioning"},{"label":"Ice Maker"},{"label":"Bow and stern bimini"}],"toys":[{"label":"Seabob F5","quantity":"1"},{"label":"Paddle surf"},{"label":"Snorkeling Equipment"},{"label":"Inflatables"}],"entertainment":["Smart TV","Wi-fi","Hi-fi"],"tenders":["Tender Ultimate 3D"]},"crew":[{"name":"Emanuele Interlando","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca352-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::23cc6f10-299d-11f0-87c8-0d2b782c78a6/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Nationality: Italian\nLanguages: Italian, English.\n\nAfter graduating from the Nautical Institute of Messina, Captain Emanuele Internando began his maritime career aboard ferry vessels before transitioning into the yachting industry. He holds all the required IMO and MCA professional certifications and has been working aboard commercial\nyachts since 2018. \n\nCaptain Internando has previously commanded Light Blue, bringing valuable familiarity with the vessel and its operations. His professional background includes extensive cruising across the Mediterranean, as well as experience in the United Arab Emirates, where he further refined his leadership and navigational expertise across both private and charter programs.\n\nIn addition to his captaincy qualifications, Emanuele is also a certified yacht surveyor, enhancing his technical knowledge and offering added value in\nthe management and maintenance of yachts under his command. Known for his discipline, professionalism, and respectful approach towards\ncrew and guests alike, Captain Internando ensures a safe, efficient, and welcoming environment on board at all times."},{"name":"Luca Colombo","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca352-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::5ff08d50-299d-11f0-87c8-0d2b782c78a6/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Nationality: Italian\nLanguages: Italian, English.\n\nLuca, our Sardinian deckhand, is a discreet yet indispensable presence on board Light Blue. Raised with a strong connection to the sea, Luca brings with him an instinctive understanding of maritime life and operations. His quiet professionalism, unwavering courtesy, and meticulous attention to detail make him a true asset to the crew.\n\nAlways present, though rarely seen, Luca ensures every element on deck is perfectly in place—from seamless moorings to immaculate maintenance. His calm demeanor, polished manners, and deep respect for the vessel and its guests create an atmosphere of understated excellence.\n\nWith Luca on board, guests can enjoy their time at sea knowing that every detail is handled with care, discretion, and genuine passion for yachting."},{"name":"Antonella Di Manso","avatar":"/media/media::image::a::vessel::d5cca352-fe8c-11ed-889f-43d4bb723744::assets::8834a080-299d-11f0-9a89-7d4c17025820/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Nationality: Italian\nLanguages: Italian, English.\n\nBorn in 1965 on the enchanting island of Ischia, near Naples, Antonella carries a proud maritime legacy as the descendant of generations of sailors and captains. With a wealth of experience in high-end hospitality and catering, she has been an essential part of Light Blue's crew since 2022.\n\nAntonella is known for her warm presence and her ability to craft culinary experiences that delight guests from breakfast through dinner. From refined Mediterranean cuisine to gourmet creations, she also holds certifications in gluten-free and Halal cuisine, ensuring all dietary needs are thoughtfully accommodated.\n\nGuests aboard Light Blue often start their day looking forward to Antonella’s breakfasts—always fresh, beautifully presented, and made with genuine passion. Her care, discretion, and deep understanding of service elevate every moment on board, making her an invaluable part of the guest experience."}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":3600000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":3600000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"EUR","price":4100000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":4100000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"July & August","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2025-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2025-08-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2026-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-08-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2027-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2027-08-31T23:59:59.999Z"}],"pricing":{"currency":"EUR","charterFee":4100000,"inputAmountTaxed":"EXCLUSIVE","note":"","unit":"WEEK","lineItems":[{"item":"Charter Fee","quantity":1,"unitPrice":4100000,"amount":4100000,"conditions":"Weekly","taxRate":{"label":"VAT","value":0.22}},{"item":"APA","conditions":"","quantity":0.35,"unitPrice":4100000,"amount":1435000}],"total":6437000,"subTotal":5535000,"totalTax":902000},"inclusionZones":[{"label":"Sardinia","type":"Geo subunit","category":["Europe","Southern Europe","Sardinia"],"coordinates":[8.96574354539669,40.12242872762209],"bbox":[8.180859375000011,38.90966796875,9.805273437500006,41.257080078125]},{"label":"Corsica","type":"Geo subunit","category":["Europe","Southern Europe","Corsica"],"coordinates":[9.104917129771797,42.161865413836736],"bbox":[8.565625000000011,41.384912109374994,9.556445312500017,43.02148437